# Test Conventions

## Imports

Always use this single import line:

```ts
import { test, expect, request, type Page, type FrameLocator, type Request } from '@playwright/test';
```

## File header

Generated specs begin with the plan + seed reference comments:

```ts
// spec: specs/<plan-file>.md
// seed: tests/seed.spec.ts
```

## Naming

- Test IDs: `TC-<AREA>-<NN>` (e.g. `TC-DB-01` dashboard UI, `TC-DV-01` Dataverse validation).
- `describe` matches the top-level plan item (e.g. `Dashboard Screen`).
- Generated test title matches the scenario name; one test per generated file.
- Include a comment with the plan step text before each step execution.

## Helper functions (reuse; do not reinvent)

- `openDashboard(page)` — navigates to app URL, waits for `Dashboard`, returns `appFrame`.
- `openCreateInvoice(page)` — navigates, clicks Create Invoice, returns `appFrame`.
- `getBillingCycleDates()` — returns `{ start, end }` ISO dates for the current billing cycle.
- `getDataverseCount(token, filterExpression)` — calls Dataverse with filter, returns count.
- `getDashboardTaskCount(page, appFrame, labelPattern)` — reads a numeric count from the
  Invoice Tasks section (the ONLY place `waitForTimeout` is allowed).
- `getLineItemCount(appFrame)` — counts line item rows on the Create Invoice form.

## Assertions

- `expect.soft` for UI structure visibility; hard `expect` for interaction/navigation.
- Prefer regex over literal counts for dynamic values.
